solution.p:
The two variables are x and y. Each column of the table shows a related pair of values. Notice that 2 is 3 less than 5, 7 is 3 less than 10, and so on.  That is:
    \begin{aligned}
               2 \amp = 5-3, \amp\amp 7 = 10-3\\
                12\amp = 15-3, \amp\amp 17 = 20-3                
                \end{aligned}
and so on. In each column, we can find y by subtracting 3 from x.  Thus,  y=x-3.
